1. Open the terminal from Jupyter Lab and type 

day4

and hit 'Enter'

2. Go to Day4 directory inside Pathways_workshop 

3. Go to gold-Au directory 

4. Inside, go to each directory one by one and run Quantum Espresso (pw.x)

5. Run pw.x on 6 cores using the mpirun command  we learnt on Day 2

mpirun -n 6 pw.x -input in > out &

6. Get the energy using the Linux command

grep ! out 

7. Save this value in the plt_energy_dist.py and plt_parabola.py python programs in the gold-Au directory.

8. Run the python programs using

python plt_energy_dist.py

python plt_parabola.py
